[size=3][u][b]Usage[/b][/u][/size]

[size=3][u][i]Direct Mode[/i][/u][/size]

In the Direct Mode, you just need to select the game folder and start playing with the Clusters relocation.
In this case the tool will load the game data directly from the game files.
The mod will be saved in the game [b]Extensions[/b] folder, under [b]relocated_clusters[/b] folder.

[size=3][u]Direct Mode First Start[/u][/size]

On the first start, the tool will inform you that you need to select the game folder, and will switch to the options menu tab.
If you will unselect [b]Direct Mode[/b] - you will go via start process in "Expert" mode: [url=https://github.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/raw/main/src/ClusterRelocationService#first-start-in-the-expert-mode]First Start in the "Expert" Mode[/url] section.

After selecting the game folder, the tool will start loading the game data.
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/first_start.gif[/img]

[size=3][u]Direct Mode First Mod Creation[/u][/size]

After loading the game data, you will see the main window and the Galaxy Map.
Please take in account - the Sectors ownership is equal to the initial game state, without any changes from the current save.
When you will be finish with the connections, you can save the mod via the [b]Mod[/b] -> [b]Save[/b] menu item.
Mod will be saved in the game [b]Extensions[/b] folder, under [b]relocated_clusters[/b] folder.

[size=3][u]Direct Mode Second and Other starts[/u][/size]

On the next starts tool will automatically load not only game data, but also the "Relocated Clusters" mod data. So, after starting you will see the the map with the already relocated clusters.

You can cancel the existing relocation, or add new, or relocated already relocated clusters.

After that you can save the mod via the [b]Mod[/b] -> [b]Save[/b] menu item.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/next_starts.gif[/img]

[size=3][u]Direct Mode To "Expert" Mode and Vice Versa[/u][/size]

At any time you can switch between the Direct Mode and the "Expert" Mode. Just go to the options menu and select or unselect the [b]Direct Mode[/b] checkbox.
Always will reload the game data and the mod data. Please take in account - in "Expert" Mode you have manually specify the mod location. And moreover, in "Expert" Mode you will work with extracted game files, not with the game files directly.

[size=3][u][i]Main Window[/i][/u][/size]

After starting, you will see the main window with a Galaxy Map.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/main_window.png[/img]

[size=3][u]Galaxy Map[/u][/size]

The Galaxy Map allows you to navigate through various sectors in the game. You can zoom in and out to view details about each sector and the gates within them. Using the map, you can select sectors to use in the gate connections.

For zooming, there are two options available:
[list]
[*] Use the slider at the top of the map.
[*] Use the mouse wheel while holding the [b]Ctrl[/b] key.
[/list]
Additionally, you can drag the map with the left mouse button when it is zoomed in.

When you click the any mouse button on a Cluster(or Sector) - it will show the [b]Context Menu[/b] with the options to [b]Mark for Relocation[/b] or [b]Cancel Relocation[/b] (if the cluster is already relocated).

If there any overlaid clusters (clusters that occupy the same space) - they will be highlighted by [b]OrangeRed[/b] border on the map.

[size=2][u][i]Relocating a Cluster[/i][/u][/size]

To relocate a cluster, you have to make a two-step process:

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/relocating_clusters.gif[/img]

[size=2][u]Marking a Cluster for Relocation[/u][/size]

To relocate a cluster, simply click on the desired cluster on the Galaxy Map and select [b]Mark for Relocation[/b] from the context menu. This action will mark the cluster for relocation, and it will be highlighted on the map.
In addition, the cell grid will be shown on the map to help you visualize the new location.

[size=2][u]Overlaid Clusters[/u][/size]

If there are any overlaid clusters (clusters that occupy the same space), they will be highlighted by [b]OrangeRed[/b] border on the map. Context menu item [b]Mark for Relocation[/b] will show as visible on map cluster, as well as a list of underlying clusters below it.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/context_menu_if_overlaid.png[/img]

[size=2][u]Choosing a New Location[/u][/size]

After marking a cluster for relocation, click on the desired empty cell on the map where you want to move the cluster. And again, a context menu will appear. Select [b]Relocate Here[/b] to move the cluster to the new location.

[size=2][u]Magic[/u][/size]

And that's it! The cluster will be relocated to the new position, and the map will update to reflect the change.
Cluster will be marked by Blue border on the map.

Previously  relocated cluster will be marked by Green border on the map.

[size=2][u]Unmark a Cluster[/u][/size]

If you change your mind and decide not to relocate a cluster, simply click on the marked cluster again and select [b]Unmark for Relocation[/b] from the context menu. This action will unmark the cluster.

Or simply [b]Mark[/b] any other cluster - the previously marked one will be unmarked automatically.

[size=2][u][i]Canceling a Relocation[/i][/u][/size]

If you want to revert a relocation and return a cluster to its original position, click on the relocated cluster and select [b]Cancel Relocation[/b] from the context menu. This action will move the cluster back to its initial location.

Please note that if the original position is already occupied by another cluster, the cancellation will not be possible. And this menu item will be disabled.

[size=3][u]Relocated Clusters List[/u][/size]

On the bottom of the main window, there is a list of relocated clusters. This list provides an overview of all clusters that have been relocated, including their names, macro ids, original and new coordinates.

[size=2][u][i]Canceling a Relocation from the List[/i][/u][/size]

To cancel a relocation from the list, simply select the desired cluster in the list and click the [b]Cancel Relocation[/b] button located right next to the list. This action will revert the selected cluster to its original position.

[size=2][u][i]Focusing on the Map from the List[/i][/u][/size]

To focus on a specific relocated cluster on the map, select the desired cluster in the list and the border of the selected item will be highlighted on the map as in a list.

[size=2][u][i]Exporting the map to the image file (png)[/i][/u][/size]

You can export the current view of the Galaxy Map to a PNG image file. This feature allows you to save and share the map view with others or use it for reference in your projects. To export the map, simply click the "Export Galaxy Map as PNG" button located at the top right corner of the Galaxy Map interface.

Thanks to [url=https://steamcommunity.com/id/sleaker]@Sleaker[/url] for the idea and initial implementation for the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/1587/]Chem Gate Builder[/url] mod.

[size=2][u][i]Hiding and showing the DLC's and Mods on a map[/i][/u][/size]

You can toggle the visibility of DLCs and Mods on the map to focus on your current editing tasks.

Please note that only hiding the Clusters and Sectors from the view, but not removing them from the game data. You will not able relocate the Clusters on the positions occupied by the hidden ones.

[size=3][u][i]Full Mess Relocation[/i][/u][/size]

You can enable or disable the "Full Mess" option, which allows you to relocate all clusters randomly in one go.
When enabled, you will see a button [b]Make a "Full Mess"[/b] under the [b]Cancel Relocation[/b] button, in the right side of the relocated clusters list.

When you press it, all clusters will be relocated one by one to random cells on the map.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/make_a_full_mess.gif[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Save the Mod[/i][/u][/size]

When you finish with the connections, you can save the mod via the [b]Mod[/b] -> [b]Save[/b] menu item. Please ensure you have completed all necessary edits before saving to avoid losing data.
After that, the mod will be saved/updated in the appropriate subfolder in the [b]Extensions[/b] folder of the game.
And can be used immediately after loading the game.

[size=3][u][i]Reload the Mod[/i][/u][/size]

If you want to break current changes at once, before they are saved - and revert to a previously saved version, you can load it via the [b]Mod[/b] -> [b]Reload[/b] menu item.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-UniverseEditor/refs/heads/main/src/ClusterRelocationService/docs/images/reload_mod.gif[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Tabs under the Galaxy Map[/i][/u][/size]

Under the Galaxy Map, there are two tabs: "Relocated Clusters" and "Overlaid Clusters".

[size=3][u]Relocated Clusters Tab[/u][/size]

The [b]Relocated Clusters[/b] tab is a primary interface for managing clusters that have been moved from their original positions. All controls related to relocated clusters are located here.

[size=3][u]Overlaid Clusters Tab[/u][/size]

The [b]Overlaid Clusters[/b] tab provides a consolidated list of cells that host multiple clusters. Entries that are currently visible on the galaxy map are shown in [b]semi-bold[/b], making it easy to spot which ones are rendered in the current view. Double-click any row to immediately center and possibly zoom-in the map on that cluster.

