[size=3][u]X4 Data Options[/u][/size]

[size=2][u][i]Game Folder Selection[/i][/u][/size]

You need to select the folder where the game is installed. This is typically the folder where the game's executable file ([b]X4.exe[/b]) is located.

You can change it any time by pressing the current folder path text.

[size=2][u][i]X4 Data Version[/i][/u][/size]

Mostly to show which game version is currently selected.

[size=2][u][i]Load Mods Data[/i][/u][/size]

You can toggle the loading of mods along with the game data and DLCs. This is useful if you want to work with mods in the tool. The mods will be loaded from the [b]extensions[/b] folder in the game folder.
Enabled by default.
Not recommended to unselect it. You can be in trouble if will place the relocated cluster on the position occupied by the modded one.

Please note that loading the mods will not make your [b]Relocated Clusters[/b] mod dependant on them. It will depend only on the DLC's and Mods which are contains the clusters you are relocating.

